atency or highfrequency trading is increasingly recognized as a key component of a modern market the number of international firms setting up operations in asia is on the rise once again after a few years of contraction but the emergence of local hft remains muted this should change as the costs of entry to all but the lowest latencies are falling the discussion points of this panel how are regional exchanges looking to work with international market makers what is behind the reemergence of international low latency firms in asia how can asian trading firms grow their low latency businesses a selection of other subjects discussed during the conference the new normal trading global markets in an age of protectionism currency derivatives managing risk in an age of volatility and reform commodities embracing volatility and the return of price inflation etfs growing liquidity in asian markets asset management evolving to deal with new challenges new bilateral margining rules and their impact on the listed markets ––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––– for more information on fow derivative world asia globalinvestorgroupcom true partner capital  global asset management true partner cboe cbot cme comex ice us chicago new york sydney tokyo hong kong singapore amsterdam chicago true partner capital usa chicago contact infochicago officetrue partner capital usa go global volatility arbitrage chicago whereas new york is deemed to be the capital of finance the real action in derivatives takes place in the windy city chicago office  amex arca box nymex nyse nyse liffe nasdaq bats phlx ise chicago new york sydney tokyo hong kong singapore amsterdam new york true partner capital new york contact infonew york officetrue partner capital go global volatility arbitrage new york there is no denying that the us economy remains the center of global attention and as such volatility of the sp  can be seen as a global proxy for market sentiment new york office  sfe asx chix australia chicago new 